FBIS4-15073 "drsov066_v_94005" FBIS-SOV-94-066 Daily Report 5 Apr 1994 Lithuania Government Indexes Wage Rate, Social Payments Government Indexes Wage Rate, Social Payments WS0604085394 Vilnius ELTA in English 2308 GMT 5 Apr 94 WS0604085394 Vilnius ELTA English BFN [From "News Bulletin" No. 471] [Text] Vilnius, April 5, ELTA -- Lithuanian Government indexed the wage rate and other social payments. From April 1 the minimum standard of living has made 48 litas a month per person. The minimum wage rate has made 53 litas, the minimum pay per hour should not be lower than 0.32 litas. Pensioners who do not work also have been allotted bigger pensions. The pensions for them have been increased by five percent.
